Boil a full #kettle{}, then pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir-fry, ~{8-10%minutes}.

After 5 mins, add the @sliced mushrooms{180%g} to the pan and cook for the remaining time, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

While the mushrooms fry, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @baby cucumber{1}, then halve lengthways. Cut lengthways into roughly 1cm wide strips, then cut into 1cm pieces widthways.

Add your cucumber to a #medium bowl{}, drizzle over the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @gochujang paste{30%g} and garlic to the chicken. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the liquid has reduced slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @spinach and ricotta ravioli{250%g} to your pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with oil and gently stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the sauce has reduced, stir the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @butter{20%g} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} into the pan. Simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Add the cooked ravioli to the sauce and stir gently to combine.

Share the ravioli between your bowls and sprinkle over the remaining hard Italian style cheese.

Toss the @wild rocket{20%g} with the cucumber and serve alongside your pasta.

Enjoy!